Park in HLAL ETF</p>\n      <p style=\"margin:0 0 12px 0;font-size:12px;color:#bfdbfe;\">Wahed FTSE USA Shariah ETF. Safe parking, diversifies concentration risk.</p>\n      <div style=\"padding:10px 14px;background-color:#1e3a5f;border-radius:6px;\">\n        <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:13px;color:#e6edf3;line-height:1.6;\"><strong>Recommended:</strong> A (if Musaffa clears MNKD) or C (if halal unverified). Deploy $247 into MNKD, keep $250 as dry powder. Don't add to VERA. <em style=\"color:#93c5fd;\">Your call.</em></p>\n      </div>\n    </td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<!-- IBKR INTELLIGENCE -->\n<tr><td style=\"padding:16px 24px 0 24px;\">\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"background-color:#0a0f1a;border-left:3px solid #3b82f6;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:16px 20px;\">\n      <p style=\"margin:0 0 4px 0;font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:#3b82f6;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;\">📊 IBKR Intelligence — Monday, July 13, 2026</p>\n      <p style=\"margin:0 0 12px 0;font-size:11px;color:#374151;font-style:italic;\">Connector unavailable — Performance, Allocation, Themes: N/A. Risk scores from portfolio.json + web research.</p>\n      <p style=\"margin:0 0 6px 0;font-size:11px;color:#64748b;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.5px;font-weight:600;\">Per-Position Risk Scores</p>\n      <table role=\"presentation\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" style=\"font-family:monospace;font-size:12px;color:#94a3b8;width:100%;\">\n        <tr><td style=\"padding:4px 0;border-bottom:1px solid #1e293b;\">VERA | <span style=\"color:#f87171;\">68/100</span> | HIGH | Post-approval commercial launch risk + ORIGIN 3 confirmatory trial Q3 2026</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding:4px 0;\">ANET | <span style=\"color:#4ade80;\">CLOSED</span> | Exited July 9 at TP1 $185 · Net +$31.56</td></tr>\n      </table>\n      <p style=\"margin:12px 0 4px 0;font-size:11px;color:#64748b;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.5px;font-weight:600;\">VERA Risk Drivers (68/100)</p>\n      <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:12px;color:#64748b;line-height:1.7;\">Valuation: Commercial-stage, no earnings yet. P/S depends on launch penetration.<br>Growth: ORIGIN 3 binary in Q3; launch ramp execution; 100% concentration.<br>Financial health: Cash burn for commercial infrastructure ahead.</p>\n    </td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<!-- WHAT TO DO TODAY -->\n<tr><td style=\"padding:16px 24px 0 24px;\">\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"background-color:#f0fdf4;border:1px solid #bbf7d0;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:16px 20px;\">\n      <p style=\"margin:0 0 6px 0;font-size:11px;color:#166534;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.5px;\">What to do today</p>\n      <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:13px;color:#14532d;line-height:1.8;\">\n        1. <strong>Verify ANET fill in IBKR</strong> → confirm 1.27 shares sold Jul 9 at $185. Then run portfolio-manager to update cash.<br>\n        2. <strong>Check VERA in IBKR</strong> — confirm price above $38 stop. No exit recommended near $42 (commission kills profit).<br>\n        3. <strong>Screen MNKD on Musaffa</strong> today. PDUFA July 26 = 13 days. Don't wait past July 20.<br>\n        4. <strong>CELC PDUFA in 4 days</strong> (July 17) — watch for sector signal: approval → biotech positive; rejection → potential VERA headwind.\n      </p>\n    </td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<!-- EDUCATION -->\n<tr><td style=\"padding:16px 24px 24px 24px;\">\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"background-color:#f1f5f9;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:20px 24px;\">\n      <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:11px;color:#475569;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.5px;\">📚 Today you learned</p>\n      <p style=\"margin:8px 0 0 0;font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;\">Price/Sales (P/S)</p>\n      <p style=\"margin:12px 0 0 0;font-size:13px;color:#1e293b;line-height:1.7;\">When a drug just got approved, P/E is meaningless — no earnings yet. P/S is the right frame: market cap divided by projected revenue. VERA's Trutakna WAC is $32,700/28-day cycle, or ~$427K/year per patient. IgAN affects ~170,000 Americans. Even 5% penetration in Year 3 = 8,500 patients × $427K = ~$3.6B annual revenue. At VERA's ~$1.5B market cap, that's roughly 0.4x forward P/S — very cheap for an approved drug if launch executes. Vertex (CFTR franchise) trades at ~6x P/S; AstraZeneca ~4x. The re-rating as quarterly launch data comes in is where the real alpha sits. Risk: launch ramp slower than modeled, or ORIGIN 3 confirmatory data disappoints in Q3.</p>\n      <p style=\"margin:12px 0 0 0;font-size:12px;color:#475569;font-style:italic;\">Also today: <strong>Revenue ramp</strong> — the pace at which a newly approved drug reaches peak penetration. Faster ramp = P/S multiple expansion. Slower ramp = multiple compression even if the science works. First quarterly patient uptake numbers (Q3 earnings) will matter more than any analyst model.</p>\n    </td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<!-- FOOTER -->\n<tr><td style=\"padding:16px 24px 24px 24px;border-top:1px solid #f3f4f6;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:10px;color:#9ca3af;line-height:1.6;\">Research output, not financial advice. Past performance does not guarantee future results. Verify halal compliance quarterly on Zoya or Musaffa. Generated Monday, July 13, 2026 — Kuwait time (UTC+3).<br>\n  <strong>Prices:</strong> IBKR connector unavailable. VERA price estimated from web sources (Jul 7–10 range $41.61–$44.60) — NOT IBKR verified. ANET fill at $185 confirmed via web research (verify in IBKR). All P&amp;L figures approximate until IBKR confirmed.<br>\n  portfolio.json last_updated: 2026-07-11T06:00:00+03:00.</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n</table>\n<